						 <p>Noting that a recent series of tags were removed, as there were a few tags missing.</p> <p>Readers, if you're not going to add <em>all</em> the tags for your article, it's best to just leave the page untagged and wait for an experienced tagger to take care of it. We have a team of people on the site who tag articles, and they search for pages that have <em>no</em> tags. Adding only a few tags prevents the team from finding the article, so if you're unfamiliar with the tags, it's totally fine to wait for them to take care of it.</p> 
				 	]]>
